2. Write an article about File Permissions based on your understanding from the notes.
Chmod u+r for adding permission
Chmod u-r for remove
>Chmod a+rwx filename
Numeric code
7 - rwx
6- rw
5- rx
4- r
3- xw
2- w
1- x
0-no

3. Read about ACL and try out the commands `getfacl` and `setfacl`
getfacl command is used to display the ACL (Access Control List) entries for a file or directory.
>getfacl filename
setfacl command is used to set or modify the ACL entries for a file or directory.
>setfacl -m u:user1:w filename